President Cyril Ramaphosa has been vaccinated for Covid-19. Ramaphosa was vaccinated at the Khayelitsha District Hospital
in Cape Town with Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize. The first 80 000 doses of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine arrived
at OR Tambo International Airport on Tuesday night, 16 February. Ramaphosa has reassured the public that the Johnson &
Johnson vaccine has been shown in extensive trials to be safe and effective. He
said they believe it will protect healthcare workers from illness and death
from Covid-19. President Cyril Ramaphosa receiving the #Covid19 vaccine. #IChooseVacciNation #VaccineRolloutSA pic.twitter.com/lYJjftWDMl 